First Lady Melania Trump visited Texas to meet with people and families affected by Hurricane Harvey. She and President Trump visited a shelter in Houston, where they donated books, crayons, and games to the children. They also helped the Red Cross serve lunch to the families in the shelter. Afterwards, they went to a distribution center in Pearland to thank volunteers and provide supplies to local families. Melania Trump donated diapers, which were in high demand at the center. They also made an impromptu stop in a neighborhood to visit with residents cleaning debris from their homes. Before leaving Texas, they met with first responders in the Coast Guard to express their gratitude. They then flew to Louisiana, where they visited a National Guard Armory and received a briefing on the state's relief efforts. Melania Trump expressed her continued thoughts and prayers for the people affected by the hurricane and pledged to provide support in the coming months.